          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Germany protests far-right</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-27-1.png" alt="Germany protests far-right" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Major German cities saw thousands of protestors while AfD had their campaign rally with a surprise guest.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The Alternative for Germany party (AfD) launched its campaign for the February 23rd elections in Halle, Germany. Cities all over Germany, such as Berlin and Cologne, protested the AfD and rising <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-h1-1-right-wing-extremism" target="_blank">right-wing extremism</a>. About 20,000 people took part in demonstrations in Cologne. Organizers had initially registered between 5,000 and 10,000 participants.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Elon Musk appeared virtually at the campaign launch for Alice Weidel‚Äôs AfD party. He said that Germany should be <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-h1-2-free-from-guilt" target="_blank">free from guilt</a> and focus on preserving the German culture and people. This brought a lot of concern as this was days after he was accused of doing the nazi salute. AfD is second in the polls behind the center-right Christian Democrat Party (CDU), which comes in at 30%.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Eyes are watching the German CDU party, which leads the election, and who it will align with. The head of the CDU party initially claimed to block the far right. However, Friedrich Merz echoes many of the same <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-h1-3-anti-migration-rhetoric" target="_blank">anti-migration rhetoric</a> as the AfD party. The AfD's official manifesto seeks faster deportations of declined asylum-seekers and those who entered the country illegally.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
