          <strong>üá∏üá∞ Slovakia's protest against their PM‚Äôs pro-Russian affiliation.</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Tensions in Slovakia have escalated as thousands protest Prime Minister Robert Fico's pro-Russia stance and recent visit to Moscow, where he met with Russian President Vladimir Putin. Demonstrations throughout Slovakia have shown <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-br1-11-widespread-opposition" target="_blank">widespread opposition</a> to his policies. Fico's critics accuse him of sabotaging Slovakia's European orientation and aligning it with Russian interests instead.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Fico‚Äôs government has stopped sending military aid to Ukraine, opposed EU sanctions on Russia, and blocked Ukraine's aspirations. These policies starkly contrast with the broader  EU position on Russia since its 2022 invasion of Ukraine. Fico has dismissed the protests, claiming they are part of a foreign-backed plot to destabilize his government.</p>
        </mj-text>
