          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>üáµüá∏ Hamas trade four hostages for 200 Palestinians in Israel detention over the weekend.</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Four Israeli female soldiers were freed by Hamas in Gaza, with Israel responding by releasing 200 Palestinian prisoners, including 121 people serving life sentences. Many saw the handover as <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-br2-12-highly-choreographed" target="_blank">highly choreographed</a> as Hamas paraded the Israeli hostages in Gaza City. Palestinians celebrated the release of prisoners in Ramallah and Gaza. The prisoner exchange and ceasefire between Israel and Hamas demonstrate the complexity of the fragile deal.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">While the hostage releases have brought relief on both sides, there are a lot of concerns that remain. Israeli forces shot and killed a Palestinian man close to the Netzarim corridor. Trump, while taking credit for the deal, now says he will send 2,000-pound bombs to Israel and suggested on Sunday that Gazans get repatriated to Jordan and Egypt to ‚Äúclean Gaza out.‚Äù</p>
