          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is the Taliban? How did they come to be?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-27-3.png" alt="What is the Taliban? How did they come to be?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-f1-13-taliban" target="_blank">Taliban</a> originated in the early 1990s in Afghanistan, formed by Islamic militants known as mujahideen, who had fought against the Soviet invasion in the 1980s. The CIA and Pakistan‚Äôs ISI backed the group. The movement attracted widespread support in the initial post-Soviet era by promising to impose stability and the rule of law.</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">They were primarily comprised of young Pashtun men who had studied in Islamic madrassas in Pakistan. They sought to restore order and imposed strict interpretations of Islamic law. The Taliban gained control of Kandahar in 1994 and captured Kabul by 1996, declaring Afghanistan an Islamic emirate under Mullah Mohammed Omar. Severe restrictions on women's rights marked their rule.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The 9/11 attack triggered the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-01-2025-f1-14-us-attack-on-taliban" target="_blank">US attack on the Taliban</a>. This systemic attack saw the Taliban overthrown by a US-led coalition in 2001 for refusing to hand over Osama bin Laden. They regrouped in Pakistan and launched an insurgency that carried on till 2014. In 2015, they agreed to a deal where the US removed most of their troops and decided to train Afghans till 2020. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The Taliban declared an ‚Äòinterim government‚Äô in Afghanistan after taking power on 15 August 2021 following the collapse of the Afghan National Security Forces and the fall of the government of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
